Went here today with Rand H.for there lunch time buffet.
The food here was your typical Chinese fare and was alright nothing i ate was terrible and at the same token nothing was outstanding.
They have good polish sausage and I liked the corn on the cob with a tray of melted butter on the side.There crispy chicken wings were also very good.
Drinks are included with the buffet which makes this a very reasonable lunch buffet and ok if your in the area.

This Buffet has never been able to get itself going very well on Yelp, which I think is a shame because the food is good here!
I have come a number of times since my initial review back in '09, & always enjoy it.
Today, Mike C. joined me.
Some positives:  *  Every time I come here, I get a cheerful greeting from the little gal that runs the place.
(She's plain, but I think she's hot!
:-))  Ok, sorry.
)  *  They now have Sushi, & the total number of food items out has increased to around 90 from 70, plus sauces & dressings!
*  Everything is good here.
Today I particularly liked the roasted peanuts for the salad, the Egg Foo Young, the Polska Keilbasa & the fried chicken.
Ok, a couple of negatives:  *  The place is getting a little run down...  torn booth upholstery, graffiti in the bathroom (not from today... we were here at opening time).
*  They have 2 TVs blabbing out Mexican soap operas all day, but you can avoid them.
(We just turned off the one that was within our hearing distance.
)  The tasty food here keeps this one at 4 Stars for me, & keeps me coming back.
No one should be giving this one less than 3 Stars, in my opinion.
Lunch Buffet $7.99/$6.99 Sr. including help-yourself soft drinks.

