= = = = = =  I eat here every so often, but it's been almost a year since an Update for them, so here's how it was today when Mike C. joined me up here for the Lunch Buffet:  *  The food was good overall, especially the broccoli salad, salad peanuts, fried chicken, the Polish (?
) Sausage, the BBQ short ribs, & the Egg Foo Young with peanut gravy.
There was a good selection of 82 food items out today, plus sauces & dressings.
With that said, a few negatives cost them a Star this time.
They need to tighten their act up a little bit:  *  It was well after the posted opening time, before they had all the food out.
(It was that way last time, too.
)  *  Had to ask them to kill the TVs blaring out Mexican soap operas.
Then another staff member turned them back on.
Then had to ask again to get them turned back down.
(This is a frequent problem with this place.
)  *  Our booth table was wobbly.
*  The water had an icky taste & needs to be filtered!
Weekday Lunch Buffet (including beverage):  $7.99/$6.99 Sr.

